<br>
You want to play a High Elf.  Guess what, in Everquest, the high elves are good, they are noble, if a bit arrogant, and upright.  The Dark Elves are evil and nasty, the Trolls are monsterous and eat people, the Iksar hate everyone and the hate is returned, etc.  You are playing Everquest, think of it being kind of like chess.  You might WANT your Knight to move like a Queen, but it doesn't, and paying 10 bucks a month doesn't change those rules no matter how you wish. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukelson13.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelson13</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 6:29:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FV Server Complaint...</span><hr size=1> &quot;i am sorry you &quot;hate&quot; this view i have, yet i am not asking you to like it. i just wanted to rp something a little more open minded than yourself. rest assured that the FV server will maintain this integrity you so crave. nothing but squeaky clean high elves everywhere....&quot;<br>
<br>
I think you've missed my point.  Your idea is OLD.  It's been done.  It's cliche.  Every 15 year old male roleplayer on earth has done it MANY TIMES.<br>
<br>
You're not expanding your mind or trying to come up with an original character concept.  You're doing the same character everyone else tries to do when they first start out roleplaying....the self-serving evil guy who couldn't care less what anyone else thinks and is such a rebel against society.  *yawn*<br>
<br>
My point wasn't that you have to fall into someone's mold.  It's that you already are and just don't realize it.<br>
<br>
Come up with something new and you will get a lot more enjoyment out of it.<br>
<br>
Verant is trying to keep it simple.  I'm not sure I agree with their choice, but I don't see it as a problem, either.  Work with it and you'll find your characters more enjoyable.<br>
<br>
Kulrick<br>
